## 4. Categories of Data Collected

The platform may collect and process the following categories of data:

- Personal data: name, identification, contact details
- Geolocation data: location of farms or users
- Agricultural data: crop type, soil conditions, farming practices
- Device and usage data: IP address, device type, app interactions
- AI-generated data: recommendations, predictive analysis, risk alerts

---

## 5. Purpose of Processing

Personal data is processed for the following purposes:

- Provide AI-based recommendations for crop management
- Detect potential crop diseases or risks
- Connect farmers with agricultural experts
- Enable transactions and access to agricultural resources
- Improve platform performance and user experience

---

## 6. Legal Basis for Processing

Processing is carried out based on:

- User consent
- Contractual necessity (service provision)
- Legitimate interests (platform improvement, fraud prevention)

---

## 7. Automated Decision-Making & AI Use

The platform uses artificial intelligence to generate insights and recommendations.

These outputs:
- Are intended as decision-support tools
- Do not replace professional judgment
- May involve automated processing of user and agricultural data

Users are informed about the existence of automated processing where applicable.

---

## 8. Data Transfers

Personal data may be transferred to third parties, including:

- Cloud infrastructure providers
- AI service providers
- External APIs and integrations

Where data is transferred outside Colombia or the EU, appropriate safeguards are implemented, such as:

- Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)
- Equivalent protection measures under Colombian law

---

## 9. Data Security Measures

The platform implements technical and organizational measures to protect personal data, including:

- Encryption (in transit and at rest)
- Access control mechanisms
- Monitoring and incident detection
- Secure development practices

---

## 10. Data Subject Rights

### Colombia (Law 1581)
Users have the right to:
- Access their data
- Update and rectify information
- Request deletion
- Revoke consent

### European Union (GDPR)
Users may exercise:
- Right of access
- Right to rectification
- Right to erasure
- Right to data portability
- Right to restriction of processing

---

## 11. Data Retention

Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law.

---

## 12. Third-Party Sharing

The platform may share data with:

- Technology providers (cloud, AI)
- Strategic partners
- Service providers involved in platform operations

All third parties are required to comply with data protection obligations.

---

## 13. Sensitive Data Considerations

Certain data processed by the platform may be considered sensitive, including:

- Geolocation data
- Agricultural production data with economic value

Additional safeguards are applied to protect such data.

---

## 14. Incident Response & Data Breaches

In the event of a data breach:

- The incident will be assessed and contained
- Users and authorities will be notified where required

### Colombia
- Notification to the Superintendence of Industry and Commerce (SIC)

### European Union
- Notification within 72 hours (GDPR requirement), where applicable

---

## 15. Policy Updates

This policy may be updated periodically. Users will be informed of significant changes through appropriate communication channels.

